==English==

===Etymology===
A reduced form of {{m|en|to cut a long story short}} and {{m|en|to make a long story short}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|En-au-long story short.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Adverb===
{{head|en|adverb}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} Introducing a short version of, or simply the conclusion of, a relevant story.
#: {{ux|en|Anyway, '''long story short''', I totally screwed up today.}}
#* {{quote-song|en|year=1980|artist=Spandau Ballet|title=To Cut a Long Story Short|album=Journeys to Glory|passage=Sitting on a park bench / Years away from fighting / Ah, to cut a '''long story short''', I lost my mind}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1994|author={{w|Eric Bogosian}}|title=Pounding Nails in the Floor With My Forehead|publisher=Theatre Communications Group|ISBN=1-55936-096-8|page=40|passage=So anyway, '''long story short''' . . . <!-- ellipsis in original --> Kenny was always gambling. And six years ago, he bought this lottery ticket and he won. Not much. A million bucks. After taxes, that’s like five hundred thousand dollars. I’m thinking party time.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1999|author=Dennis Hensley|title=Misadventures in [[w:Area code 213|the (213)]]|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=EmUaVkRgMLsC|publisher=HarperCollins| ISBN=0-688-17128-1|page=74|passage=“So '''long story short''',” Damon continues, obviously enjoying his newfound status as Magic Kingdom iconoclast, “it got back to the director what I did and then it went all the way to [Michael] Eisner’s office. {{...}}”}}
#* {{quote-av|en|date=2005 March 1|title={{w|Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs}}|medium=television production|season=4|number=19|episode=My Best Laid Plans|actor=Ken Jenkins|role=Dr. Kelso|passage='''Long story short''', I'm on the hook for sending Trong Tri Kelso to college and he doesn't want to go to a state school.}}

